The thing that shocked me the most about my research on cybercrime was how easy and psychological many scams are. Fraudsters frequently rely less on technical hacking skills and more on fear and urgency. For instance, victims of UPI frauds voluntarily consent to payments out of confusion or coercion without understanding the repercussions. This demonstrates that in preventing such crimes, awareness is frequently more crucial than technology.

Being more cautious before making any financial decisions online is one habit I will personally alter as a result. I'll always double-check payment information, confirm requests, and refrain from acting rashly under duress. In addition to safeguarding my finances, forming this habit will enhance my general digital discipline.
